parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or near-miss incidents, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels hard or unresponsive
the brake pedal only depresses a short distance
the vehicle does not stop or slows down significantly
the ABS warning light is illuminated on the dashboard
the brake system fails to function
and the vehicle is unable to stop.

symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rust corrosion of the engine cradle can lead to structural failure, causing the engine to shift or drop, potentially resulting in loss of vehicle control, accidents, or engine damage.
symptoms: Rattling or clunking noises from the engine area

engine sagging or leaning
rust or corrosion visible on the engine cradle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inoperability of the seat belt buckle can prevent the proper restraint of the driver, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The male end of the seat belt buckle will not insert into the female portion
the seat belt buckle is stuck
